1
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,840
Immature mindset

2
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:40,200
Unreasonable, thick-skinned too

3
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,800
All of this needs deep self-reflection

4
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,840
And proper self-criticism

5
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,680
Fine, let's hear it.

6
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:48,080
As for money, I really have none.

7
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,280
But I really want to get this done.

8
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,680
So how can you help me?

9
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:53,080
You need the right attitude when asking a favor.

10
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:56,240
With my handsome looks,

11
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,120
and my noble soul,

12
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,640
don't I deserve some praise?

13
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,440
Praise, huh?

14
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,480
Fine.

15
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,720
Xuan Yan is the most handsome.

16
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:07,080
Xuan Yan is the most capable.

17
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,880
Xuan Yan...

18
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:08,840
Xuan Yan...

19
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,440
Put more heart into it.

20
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,160
Xuan Yan...

21
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,680
A bit more emotion.

22
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,600
Xuan, Xuan.

23
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:16,280
Pigs might fly.

24
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:20,680
Little Lin actually knows how to compliment people.

25
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,400
Brother Min!

26
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,440
How's that? Jealous?

27
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,280
She chased me all the way home to confess her love.

28
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:31,600
Who?

29
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:32,480
Little Lin.

30
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,600
You confessed to him?

31
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,720
Impressive, impressive!

32
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:37,040
I'm so jealous.

33
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:39,760
This is the first time I've heard you praise anyone.

34
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,920
Why don't you praise me too?

35
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:43,080
Just say, "Brother Min,

36
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,360
you're better than Xuan Yan.

37
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,720
You're more capable than Xuan Yan.

38
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:47,160
You're more handsome than Xuan Yan."

39
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:48,920
Fine, fine, Brother Min.

40
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,440
I can't be bothered to explain.

41
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,080
You two just keep chatting.

42
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,480
See you on-site tomorrow.

43
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,520
You'd better design it properly.

44
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,800
Or else, just you wait.

45
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,080
I'm off, Brother Min.

46
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,080
Don't go!

47
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,400
Isn't that playing favorites?

48
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:01,520
She turns on a dime!

49
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:02,280
Over here,

50
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,360
we plan to create the Literati Gathering

51
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,720
and Literary Mind Workshop themed zones.

52
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,680
As for the AR treasure-hunt game,

53
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,840
it blends the Four Treasures of the Study culture

54
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:13,760
with fun for a deeply interactive experience.

55
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,040
It includes the Xuan Paper Code,

56
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:19,080
Magic Brush Restoration, Quest for Authenticity,

57
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,760
and Ink Formation Breakout, four chapters in all.

58
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,040
That sounds pretty lively!

59
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:23,560
Yes.

60
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,160
Has the promotion campaign kicked off yet?

61
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,640
Absolutely, Secretary Peng.

62
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:29,920
On online platforms, we've launched

63
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,400
the Four Treasures Upgrade Plan

64
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,200
and the Call to Arms of the Ink and Paper World.

65
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:33,640
Oh, right.

66
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,080
On short-video apps,

67
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:37,040
we've created four brand-new accounts,

68
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:38,400
updated daily.

69
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,200
Currently, our follower count has reached

70
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,480
over 500,000.

71
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,600
And it's expected to keep

72
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,400
growing, growing, and growing.

73
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,240
Wonderful!

74
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,600
Little Peach, keep it up!

75
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:47,160
Keep it up!

76
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,800
How many people are expected on opening day?

77
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,280
We estimate...

78
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,080
Conservatively speaking,

79
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,280
apart from the Four Treasures

80
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,280
industry insiders who've registered,

81
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,840
daily new visitors won't be under a thousand.

82
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,760
But that's just a conservative estimate.

83
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,400
If it goes viral,

84
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,480
it could easily grow more than tenfold.

85
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,440
Tenfold?

86
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:08,480
That sounds like a lot of people.

87
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,120
Yes.

88
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,120
If it were older folks,

89
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,600
it wouldn't matter how many came.

90
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,920
But if thousands upon thousands

91
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,200
of young people suddenly pour in,

92
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,279
this venue might get turned upside down.

93
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,399
That'd be great!

94
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,920
We couldn't ask for more.

95
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,400
That's exactly the buzz we want.

96
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:24,960
Secretary Peng,

97
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,040
for the Literati Gathering and Literary Mind Workshop,

98
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:29,040
I specifically got Xuan Yan to design them.

99
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,000
He's right over there.

100
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,760
Really?

101
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,320
You can't just leave it lying around.

102
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:32,960
Xuan Yan!

103
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:33,440
When the time comes...

104
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:33,800
Xuan Yan!

105
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,520
Come here, quick!

106
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,200
The leaders are here.

107
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,080
Do as I said, alright?

108
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:37,480
Okay, okay.

109
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,080
Got it.

110
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:39,840
Secretary Peng.

111
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:40,600
Take a look.

112
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:45,080
Having a talent like you join us,

113
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,600
I couldn't ask for more.

114
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,400
Not at all.

115
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,120
Come, come.

116
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,360
Thank you for your hard work.

117
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,120
You see, with you here,

118
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,560
how could our Four Treasures Festival

119
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,600
not be a huge hit?

120
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,880
No, no, no.

121
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:55,520
You flatter me.

122
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,080
Knowing Xuan Yan would come,

123
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,400
we were all thrilled.

124
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,880
Everyone's got more confidence now.

125
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,680
Yes, yes.

126
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,720
Go, God Yan!

127
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:04,920
Go, go, go!

128
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,360
Look, so many people.

129
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,600
Mostly just taking a break.

130
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:11,520
It's Director Lin's PR skills that are impressive.

131
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,360
I don't quite see it that way.

132
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,360
Actually,

133
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,440
Peach Blossom Town is our shared home.

134
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:17,160
So,

135
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,360
we must work together to build it well.

136
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:20,840
Right?

137
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,240
Exactly, the Secretary is right.

138
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,800
Since all the leaders are here today,

139
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,520
let me

140
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,560
give everyone a report.

141
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,160
Good, good.

142
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:28,160
For this Literati Gathering,

143
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:30,520
my design uses the Four Treasures as the framework,

144
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:31,840
refined taste as the soul,

145
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,640
with objects conveying meaning as the core concept.

146
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,720
It includes the Literary Mind Workshop,

147
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,440
the Ink Rhythm Battlefield,

148
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,800
Cosplay, and other themed sections, six in total.

149
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:39,920
Little Lin,

150
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:43,160
besides funding, what other difficulties do we have?

151
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,600
I think the biggest issue

152
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,360
is still funding.

153
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,240
Take the AR equipment, for example,

154
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:51,600
much of it needs to be installed and tested ASAP.

155
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,720
And the Literati Gathering that Xuan Yan handles,

156
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,600
many scenes require set building.

157
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,600
Tight schedule, heavy workload.

158
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,160
The workload is simply too much right now.

159
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,160
Secretary Peng specifically held

160
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,040
a major decision-making meeting for this.

161
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,200
She's already found ways to squeeze funds

162
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,880
from investment and publicity budgets.

163
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,760
Secretary Peng also stated at the meeting

164
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:12,440
that no matter how tight or difficult things are,

165
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,440
we must first ensure

166
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,880
the smooth progress of the Four Treasures Festival.

167
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:16,960
Right.

168
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,320
Don't be too anxious.

169
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,640
The funds are being raised right now.

170
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,680
The process takes time.

171
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,880
We'll definitely do our best.

172
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,560
The meal expenses

173
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,760
have all been fronted by Lin Yiran.

174
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,920
She has a sick old mother at home.

175
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:33,080
How much money can she afford to front?

176
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,560
What's going on?

177
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,680
Why is Lin Yiran fronting this money?

178
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,240
At the very beginning,

179
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,120
weren't we eating at the cafeteria?

180
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,360
Later, considering work efficiency,

181
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,640
we made a temporary adjustment.

182
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,240
The coordination fell behind.

183
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,120
Yiran, stop ordering the meals.

184
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,360
I'll get this sorted for you.

185
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,080
Next time something like this happens,

186
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,000
just tell me directly, okay?

187
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,800
This is unacceptable.

188
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,240
How can we let an individual front meal expenses?

189
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:57,920
Right, right.

190
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:59,360
This is my responsibility too.

191
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,400
Secretary.

192
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,840
I've got some concerns.

193
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,160
I've been mulling it over for a while.

194
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,280
Not sure if I should bring it up.

195
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,320
What is it? Just say it.

196
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,360
The Xuan paper market area

197
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,280
is only so big.

198
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,400
If it really goes like Director Lin says,

199
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,400
and on opening day,

200
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:34,200
thousands of young people flood in at once,

201
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,960
how are we supposed to control the crowd?

202
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:37,800
This is no small matter.

203
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,400
Look, on opening day,

204
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,320
provincial leaders are coming.

205
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,320
Key city and county leaders are coming too.

206
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,240
If anything goes wrong,

207
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,080
who could shoulder the responsibility?

208
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,440
Security, reception, fire safety,

209
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:53,240
isn't the county directly in charge?

210
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:53,880
Yes.

211
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,760
Well, the county is worried too.

212
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:58,800
I'm not worried about anything else.

213
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,320
It's this bunch of young people I worry about.

214
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,760
Never mind whether security's manageable.

215
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,560
Just the cosplay performance Xuan Yan mentioned,

216
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,760
I've got some issues with that.

217
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,640
You don't know, but I have a niece.

218
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:12,000
She's really into cosplay.

219
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,760
Wherever there's a gathering in the country,

220
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:14,760
she'd rush right over.

221
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,240
Their makeup, you probably haven't seen it.

222
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:17,880
Smeared all over,

223
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:20,000
faces covered in blood, all gory.

224
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,920
It'd give you a heart...

225
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,720
Right.

226
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,120
This, this...

227
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,080
Just my personal view.

228
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,640
Deputy Mayor Luo,

229
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,640
I actually think

230
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,880
your perspective is a bit off.

231
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:37,200
I think the more young people, the better.

232
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,360
Young people are the future of our nation.

233
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,800
Look at our Peach Blossom Town's Xuan paper,

234
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,240
passed down for a thousand years,

235
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,360
with such a unique advantage.

236
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,240
What we need now is to build a platform,

237
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:55,000
let more young people learn about it,

238
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,560
and come to love our

239
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,000
intangible heritage and traditional culture.

240
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,680
Right.

241
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,320
After all, going forward,

242
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:03,520
we rely on the youth to carry it on.

243
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,400
Right?

244
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,760
Right, right, right.

245
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,000
As for the headcount being uncertain,

246
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,760
let Lin Yiran and her team estimate it.

247
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,440
If anything comes up,

248
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,880
report it to the county promptly.

249
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,520
Deputy Mayor Luo,

250
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,680
I want to emphasize this again.

251
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:25,760
Don't hold such prejudices against the youth.

252
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,240
They're young, you know.

253
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,680
Let them go for it.

254
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,440
Support them, understand them.

255
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,360
Plan ahead.

256
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,760
Do the work the way it should be done.

257
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,440
We've already opened the restaurant.

258
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,240
Are we afraid of customers coming to eat?

259
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:38,680
Right, right.

260
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,000
Everything you said is correct.

261
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,640
Actually, it's not really prejudice.

262
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,680
Deputy Mayor Luo,

263
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,880
You have a meeting at the county soon, right?

264
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:46,760
Have Master Wang drive you there.

265
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,080
No need to call a separate car.

266
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:50,880
Well, I...

267
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,160
Boss.

268
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:08,280
Weigh me out some tripe.

269
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,240
And these chicken feet too.

270
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,920
And weigh out some of this cold salad.

271
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:14,680
Thanks.

272
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,480
Is this salt-water chicken?

273
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,000
Yes.

274
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,480
Give me one of these too.

275
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,600
Right.

276
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,240
Have Wang Hao keep an eye on it.

277
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,240
Look at the third row.

278
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,720
There's actually a problem with it.

279
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,120
If you're not sure,

280
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,120
just wait till I get back.

281
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:28,880
I'll be quick.

282
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,160
Excuse me, could you speed it up a bit?

283
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,720
I'm a bit pressed for time. Thanks.

284
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,600
Sure thing.

285
